<HEADLINE>
NCKU TO HOST STUDENT FORUM FOR GLOBAL SUSTAINABILITY 2007
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taipei, May 17 (CNA) 05/17/07  18:21:50 (By Deborah Kuo)
</P>
<P>
A student forum for global sustainability is scheduled to be held
at National Cheng Kung University (NCKU) in Tainan City, southern
Taiwan, with about 100 university students from Taiwan, Japan,
Hong Kong and China participating, an NCKU student activity
source said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The NCKU Student Forum for Global Sustainability 2007 will
feature two sub- forums -- sustainability for Taiwan and the
world and an East Asia teleconference forum -- according to NCKU
sponsors.
</P>
<P>
Two main topics -- the future of Taiwan's sustainability under
the influence of globalization and how college students can
create an East Asian link-up -- will be mooted during the forum,
the sponsors said.
</P>
<P>
The students from Japan, Hong Kong and China will be representing
the University of Tokyo Students Community, the Alliance for
Global Sustainability of the University of Tokyo, the Hong Kong
Green Student Council,  Fudan University, the Dalian University
of Technology,  Shandong University, Jilin University and
Zhejiang University.
</P>
<P>
Local students who are expected to take part in the forum will be
from NCKU, National Taiwan University, National Chengchi
University, National Sun Yat-sen University and Nanhua
University, according to the sponsors.
</P>
